094">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/24608306/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Management+and+outcome+of+pouch-vaginal+fistulas+after+IPAA+surgery&amp;author=IH+Mallick&amp;author=TL+Hull&amp;author=FH+Remzi&amp;author=RP+Kiran&amp;publication_year=2014&amp;journal=Dis+Colon+Rectum&amp;pages=490-496&amp;doi=10.1097%2FDCR.0000000000000094&amp;pmid=24608306">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">38.</div><div id="r38" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Kammann S, Menias C, Hara A, et al. Genital and reproductive organ complications of Crohn disease: technical considerations as it relates to perianal disease, imaging features, and implications on management. <em>Abdom Radiol (NY)</em> 2017;42(6):1752–1761.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s00261-017-1073-z">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/28194515/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Genital+and+reproductive+organ+complications+of+Crohn+disease%3A+technical+considerations+as+it+relates+to+perianal+disease%2C+imaging+features%2C+and+implications+on+management&amp;author=S+Kammann&amp;author=C+Menias&amp;author=A+Hara&amp;publication_year=2017&amp;journal=Abdom+Radiol+%28NY%29&amp;pages=1752-1761&amp;doi=10.1007%2Fs00261-017-1073-z&amp;pmid=28194515">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">39.</div><div id="r39" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Pastor DM, Lowry AC. Surgical management of rectovaginal fistula. <em>Semin Colon Rectal Surg</em> 2014;25(4):221–227.</div><div class="external-